From ca2506cd4a31b53857d2fc1c6da3bd1c505a4f61 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <claude@anthropic.com>
Date: Tue, 14 Jul 2026 19:36:27 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Rework Pinpress: photos-first workflow + face-area guide

- Replace quantities-first flow with photos -> sizes/qty -> align -> print
- New data model: appState.photos[] + appState.groups[] (one group per
  photo+type combo; qty expanded into instances only at print time)
- Step 3 now shows one tile per (photo, type) group instead of per-instance,
  so N copies of the same photo/size share one alignment
- Add face-area guide in the editor: dimmed bleed ring + dashed face
  outline on its own Konva layer, never touching drawInstanceImage() or
  the export path; togglable, on by default
- Add 'Reset position' button in the editor; remove the old
  'also fill N more slots' duplicate control (superseded by Step 2 qty)
- Move the edge-margin toggle from Step 1 to Step 4 (it's a printer
  property, not a photo property)
- Minimal, backward-compatible extension to tracePunchShape() (optional
  skipBeginPath arg) so the face guide's scrim can even-odd fill a
  punch-minus-face compound path; every existing call site unaffected
- drawInstanceImage(), packInstances(), getPrintableRect(),
  renderInstanceToDataURL(), generatePDF() core logic unchanged
